Theorem 36.Theorem:
Let $a_{1} \leq a_{2} \leq \cdots \leq a_{n}$ and $b_{1} \leq$ $b_{2} \leq \cdots \leq b_{n}$ be real numbers. For any permutation $\left(x_{1}, x_{2}, \ldots, x_{n}\right)$ of $\left(a_{1}, a_{2}, \ldots, a_{n}\right)$ we have the following inequalities:
$$
\begin{aligned}
a_{1} b_{1}+a_{2} b_{2}+\cdots+a_{n} b_{n} & \geq x_{1} b_{1}+x_{2} b_{2}+\cdots+x_{n} b_{n} \\
& \geq a_{n} b_{1}+a_{n-1} b_{2}+\cdots+a_{1} b_{n}
\end{aligned}
$$
